4) Three conscious reviewer acceptances

 1. Surefire IT-gate in pom.xml: *IT now runs in CI path used today (mvn package), so behavioral net is no longer silently skipped.
 2. Dead @SecureWithTokens is pre-existing: escalated separately; not introduced by this migration.
 3. Safety net is test-only / zero-prod: contract/smoke fixtures and ITs are verification surface, not runtime feature change.

