5) What was verified and how

 - Serialization vectors were pinned to Boot 3.5 captures and compared on Boot 4 (provenance trail in baseline document).
 - Covered vectors include field ordering, naming, null handling, record output, enum/property mapping, BigDecimal rendering.
 - Residuals were explicitly classified (including pre-existing SFTP test gap and accepted Double serialization residual) in closed verification evidence.

Primary evidence artifacts:

 - baseline-provenance.md (Boot 3.5 capture provenance and fixture lineage),
 - verification-closed.md (closed verdict + vector-by-vector evidence),
 - compatibility-decisions.md (version/pin/coord rationale for migration decisions).

